field.value:
Consider a class like:

public class Foo
{
	public virtual void DoSomething<T>(Expression<Func<T,bool>> filter)
	{
	}
}

Note that the generic parameter 'T' in DoSomething is used in declaration of the method parameter as a generic parameter of Func<,> which is itself the generic parameter for Expression<>.

Now, if you create a class proxy from Foo, you'll get the following BadImageFormatException upon call to DoSomething:

An attempt was made to load a program with an incorrect format. (Exception from HRESULT: 0x8007000B)


Note that if DoSomething is like the following:

public virtual void DoSomething<T>(Func<T,bool> filter);

or this:

public virtual void DoSomething<T>(T filter);


the generated proxy works without any problems. I have tested the latest revision(5967) and it had the same problem.
